      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Aspect-Based Sentiment Analysis (ABSA)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "ABSA decomposes a review into (aspect, sentiment) pairs. A simple extraction pipeline uses a dependency parser to find opinion targets and an auxiliary sentiment classifier per span:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# pip install pyabsa\nfrom pyabsa import AspectSentimentTripletExtraction as ASTE\n\n# Uses a pretrained ASTE model (English restaurant/laptop domains)\nextractor = ASTE.AspectSentimentTripletExtractor(\n    checkpoint=\"fast_lsa_t_v2\"\n)\n\nresult = extractor.predict([\n    \"The battery life is excellent but the camera is disappointing.\"\n])\nprint(result[0][\"triplets\"])\n# [('battery life', 'excellent', 'positive'),\n#  ('camera', 'disappointing', 'negative')]"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "For production ABSA without a specialized library, the standard approach is to frame it as a reading-comprehension task: the aspect is the \"question\" and the model extracts a sentiment span from the review."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
